article.headline: Yale 58, Dartmouth 54
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. (AP) -- Alex Gamboa had 15 points on 5-of-7 shooting to lead Yale to a 58-54 Ivy League win over Dartmouth Saturday. Gamboa scored Yale's final five points that included hitting 3 of 4 free throws in the final 27 seconds to secure the win for the Bulldogs (11-14, 6-6 Ivy). Dartmouth (3-23, 1-11) has lost 16 straight. The Big Green, which had a 29-23 lead at the break, was led by Michael McLaren and Michael Lang, who each had 12 points. McLaren's 3-pointer from the top of the key with 1:36 left pulled Dartmouth within 53-52. The Bulldogs built the lead to 56-52 and held on when Yale's Matt Minoff blocked a 3-point attempt by Leon Pattman at the top of the key with 19 seconds left. Seldom-used sophomore center Dexter Upshaw scored a career-high 11 points for Yale.
